3.2 VULNERABILITY OVERVIEW
3.2.1    USE OF INSUFFICIENTLY RANDOM VALUES CWE-330The application suffers from weak random values that can affect the confidentiality and integrity of data stored on the device.CVE-2018-20025 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 9.4 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:L).3.2.2    IMPROPER RESTRICTION OF COMMUNICATION CHANNEL TO INTENDED ENDPOINTS CWE-923The application does not properly restrict communication channels, allowing the source of communication packets to be spoofed.CVE-2018-20026 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 5.8 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:N/A:N).
